<p>
<seg id=1> Palestine Leader Arafat began his first official flight taking off from Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=2> The Gaza International Airport came into use the day before. </seg>
<seg id=3> Israeli security officials saw the special plane of Arafat taking off for Paris from the runway on Wednesday. </seg>
<seg id=4> Israel presides over the security of the airport. </seg>
<seg id=5> The newly subscribed Land-for-Peace Agreement paved the way for the Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=6> The airport is held by Palestinians as a symbol of their national sovereignty, which is also a stimulus for Palestinian economy. </seg>
</p>
